Quote: Old Chum. - Man who has a long experience of the Colony. Not used except as opposite of new chum. `Never was a freshman at Cambridge more anxious to be mistaken for a third year man, than I was anxious to become an old chum, as the Colonial dialect calls a settler--thereby proving  my new chumship most satisfactorily.'--Butler A First Year in Canterbury Settlement], p. 54. ([[1898 Morris Austral-English]
